1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Uranium dating reveals ages that carbon can't even touch.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:05,600
Geochronology is all about timing—literally.

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:10,800
While carbon dating stops at about 50,000 years, uranium-lead dating goes back billions.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,400
Imagine rocks that formed when dinosaurs roamed...or even before!

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,800
This method unlocks Earth’s deepest history.

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,400
Uranium decays slowly over time, providing a reliable clock.

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:25,200
Scientists use it to date zircon crystals—some over 4 billion years old!

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:32,400
So next time you think of ancient time, remember: uranium-lead dating is the key to Earth's age-old secrets.

9
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,800
Want to dive deeper into geology?

10
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:39,600
